  description: A nearly perfect sphere of hot plasma at the center of our solar system.
    It accounts for roughly 99.86% of the total mass of the entire solar system.
    Its gravity holds everything from giant planets to tiny debris in orbit, and
    its core reaches temperatures over 15 million degrees Celsius, driving the nuclear
    fusion that sustains life on Earth.
